#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:3
msgid "vtkModuleTesting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:5
msgid ""
"VTK uses the ExternalData_ CMake module to handle the data management for "
"its test suite. Test data is only downloaded when a test which requires it "
"is enabled and it is cached so that every build does not need to redownload "
"the same data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:10
msgid ""
"To facilitate this workflow, there are a number of CMake functions available "
"in order to indicate that test data is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:51
msgid "Loading data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:54
msgid "Download test data. |module|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:56
msgid "Data may be downloaded manually using this function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:58
msgid "vtk_module_test_data(<PATHSPEC>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:62
msgid ""
"This will download data inside of the input data directory for the modules "
"being built at that time (see the ``TEST_INPUT_DATA_DIRECTORY`` argument of "
"``vtk_module_build``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:66
msgid ""
"For supported `PATHSPEC` syntax, see the associated documentation in ref:"
"`ExternalData`. These arguments are already wrapped in the ``DATA{}`` syntax "
"and are assumed to be relative paths from the input data directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:99
msgid "Creating test executables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:103
msgid ""
"This function creates an executable from the list of sources passed to it. "
"It is automatically linked to the module the tests are intended for as well "
"as any declared test dependencies of the module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:107
msgid "vtk_module_test_executable(<NAME> <SOURCE>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:111
msgid ""
"This function is not usually used directly, but instead through the other "
"convenience functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:162
msgid "Test name parsing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:164
msgid ""
"Test names default to using the basename of the filename which contains the "
"test. Two tests may share the same file by prefixing with a custom name for "
"the test and a comma."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:168
msgid ""
"The two parsed syntaxes are: - ``CustomTestName,TestFile`` - ``TestFile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:172
msgid ""
"Note that ``TestFile`` should already have had its extension stripped "
"(usually done by ``_vtk_test_parse_args``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:175
msgid ""
"In general, the name of a test will be ``<EXENAME>-<TESTNAME>``, however, by "
"setting ``vtk_test_prefix``, the test name will instead be ``<EXENAME>-"
"<PREFIX><TESTNAME>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:212
msgid "Test function arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:214
msgid "Each test is specified  using one of the two following syntaxes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:216
msgid "``<NAME>.<SOURCE_EXT>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:217
msgid "``<NAME>.<SOURCE_EXT>,<OPTIONS>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:219
msgid ""
"Where ``NAME`` is a valid test name. If present, the specified ``OPTIONS`` "
"are only for the associated test. The expected extension is specified by the "
"associated test function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:228
msgid ""
"|module-internal| Given a list of valid \"options\", this function will "
"parse out a the following variables:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:232
msgid ""
"``args``: Unrecognized arguments. These should be interpreted as arguments "
"that should be passed on the command line to all tests in this parse group."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:234
msgid "``options``: Options specified globally (for all tests in this group)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:235
msgid ""
"``names``: A list containing all named tests. These should be parsed by "
"``_vtk_test_parse_name``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:237
msgid "``_<NAME>_options``: Options specific to a certain test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:239
msgid "_vtk_test_parse_args(<OPTIONS> <SOURCE_EXT> <ARG>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:243
msgid ""
"In order to be recognized as a source file, the ``SOURCE_EXT`` must be used. "
"Without it, all non-option arguments are placed into ``args``. Each test is "
"parsed out matching these:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:287
msgid ""
"For handling global option settings |module-internal|, this function sets "
"variables in the calling scoped named `<PREFIX><OPTION>` to either `0` or "
"`1` if the option is present in the remaining argument list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:291
msgid "_vtk_test_set_options(<OPTIONS> <PREFIX> <ARG>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:295
msgid ""
"Additionally, a non-`0` default for a given option may be specified by a "
"variable with the same name as the option and specifying a prefix for the "
"output variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:330
msgid "C++ tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:334
msgid ""
"This function declares C++ tests |module|. Source files are required to use "
"the `cxx` extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:337
msgid "vtk_add_test_cxx(<EXENAME> <VARNAME> <ARG>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:341
#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:522
msgid ""
"Each argument should be either an option, a test specification, or it is "
"passed as flags to all tests declared in the group. The list of tests is set "
"in the ``<VARNAME>`` variable in the calling scope."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:345
#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:526
#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1054
msgid "Options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:347
msgid ""
"``NO_DATA``: The test does not need to know the test input data directory. "
"If it does, it is passed on the command line via the ``-D`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:349
msgid ""
"``NO_VALID``: The test does not have a valid baseline image. If it does, the "
"baseline is assumed to be in ``../Data/Baseline/<NAME>.png`` relative to the "
"current source directory. If alternate baseline images are required, "
"``<NAME>`` may be suffixed by ``_1``, ``_2``, etc. The valid image is passed "
"via the ``-V`` flag. - ``TIGHT_VALID``: Uses euclidean type metrics to "
"compare baselines. Baseline comparison is sensitive to outliers in this "
"setting. - ``LOOSE_VALID``: Uses L1 type metrics to compare baselines. "
"Baseline comparison is somewhat more forgiving. Typical use cases involve "
"rendering that is highly GPU dependent, and baselines with text. - "
"``LEGACY_VALID``: Uses legacy image compare. This metric generates a lot of "
"false negatives. It is recommended not to use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:361
msgid ""
"``NO_OUTPUT``: The test does not need to write out any data to the "
"filesystem. If it does, a directory which may be written to is passed via "
"the ``-T`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:364
msgid ""
"``WEBGPU_GRAPHICS_BACKEND``: The test should be run using the WebGPU "
"graphics backend. This is only available when building with WebGPU support. "
"It enables WebGPU via setting the environment variable "
"``VTK_GRAPHICS_BACKEND=WEBGPU``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:368
msgid ""
"Additional flags may be passed to tests using the ``${_vtk_build_test}"
"_ARGS`` variable or the ``<NAME>_ARGS`` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:511
#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1000
msgid "MPI tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:515
msgid ""
"This function declares C++ tests which should be run under an MPI "
"environment. |module| Source files are required to use the `cxx` extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:518
msgid "vtk_add_test_mpi(<EXENAME> <VARNAME> <ARG>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:528
msgid "``TESTING_DATA``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:529
msgid ""
"``NO_VALID``: The test does not have a valid baseline image. If it does, the "
"baseline is assumed to be in ``../Data/Baseline/<NAME>.png`` relative to the "
"current source directory. If alternate baseline images are required, "
"``<NAME>`` may be suffixed by ``_1``, ``_2``, etc. The valid image is passed "
"via the ``-V`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:535
msgid ""
"Each test is run using the number of processors specified by the following "
"variables (using the first one which is set):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:538
msgid "``<NAME>_NUMPROCS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:539
msgid "``<EXENAME>_NUMPROCS``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:540
msgid "``VTK_MPI_NUMPROCS`` (defaults to ``2``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:542
msgid ""
"Additional flags may be passed to tests using the ``${_vtk_build_test}"
"_ARGS`` variable or the `<NAME>_ARGS` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:639
msgid "C++ test executable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:643
msgid ""
"vtk_test_cxx_executable(<EXENAME> <VARNAME> [RENDERING_FACTORY] [<SRC>...])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:647
msgid ""
"Creates an executable named ``EXENAME`` which contains the tests listed in "
"the variable named in the ``VARNAME`` argument. The ``EXENAME`` must match "
"the ``EXENAME`` passed to the test declarations when building the list of "
"tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:651
msgid ""
"If ``RENDERING_FACTORY`` is provided, VTK's rendering factories are "
"initialized during the test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:654
msgid ""
"By default, VTK's rendering tests enable FP exceptions to find floating "
"point errors in debug builds. If ``DISABLE_FLOATING_POINT_EXCEPTIONS`` is "
"provided, FP exceptions are not enabled for the test. This is useful when "
"testing against external libraries to ignore exceptions in third-party code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:659
msgid ""
"Any additional arguments are added as additional sources for the executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:698
msgid ""
"MPI executables used to have their own test executable function.|module-"
"internal| This is no longer necessary and is deprecated. Instead, "
"`vtk_test_cxx_executable` should be used instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:712
msgid "Python tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:716
msgid ""
"This function declares Python tests.|module| Test files are required to use "
"the `py` extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:719
msgid "vtk_add_test_python(<EXENAME> <VARNAME> <ARG>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:725
msgid ""
"If the ``_vtk_testing_python_exe`` variable is not set, the ``vtkpython`` "
"binary is used by default. Additional arguments may be passed in this "
"variable as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:728
msgid ""
"If the given Python executable supports VTK's ``--enable-bt`` flag, setting "
"``_vtk_testing_python_exe_supports_bt`` to ``1`` is required to enable it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:914
msgid "JavaScript tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:918
msgid ""
"This function declares JavaScript tests run with NodeJS. Test files are "
"required to use the `mjs` extension. Additional arguments to `node` can be "
"passed via `_vtk_node_args` variable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:922
msgid "vtk_add_test_module_javascript_node(<VARNAME> <ARG>...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:928
msgid ""
"The ``_vtk_testing_nodejs_exe`` variable must point to the path of a `node` "
"interpreter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1004
msgid ""
"A small wrapper around ``vtk_add_test_python`` which adds support for "
"running MPI-aware tests written in Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1007
msgid ""
"The ``$<module library name>_NUMPROCS`` variable may be used to use a non-"
"default number of processors for a test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1010
msgid "This forces running with the ``pvtkpython`` executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1037
msgid "ABI Mangling tests"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1041
msgid ""
"This function declares a test to verify that all of the exported symbols in "
"the VTK module library contain the correct ABI mangling prefix. This test "
"requires setting the option VTK_ABI_NAMESPACE_NAME to a value that is not "
"\"<DEFAULT>\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1045
msgid ""
"Current limitations of this test are: - Does not run on non-UNIX platforms - "
"Is not compatible with the option \"VTK_ENABLE_KITS\" - May not work outside "
"of VTK itself"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1050
msgid "vtk_add_test_mangling(module_name [EXEMPTIONS ...])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../CMake/vtkModuleTesting.cmake:1056
msgid ""
"``EXEMPTIONS``: List of symbol patterns to excluded from the ABI mangling "
"test where it is known that the symbols do not support the ABI mangling but "
"are still exported. This option should be extremely rare to use, see the "
"documentation on ABI mangling for how the handle C and C++ symbols before "
"adding an EXEMPTION."
msgstr ""
